{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Azs2HBfp8zD7reSELJzXeD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. **EntityController** \n**File:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/EntityController.java`\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `POST /api/v1/entities/query` — Query failed entities (pagination)\n- `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}` — Get entity by ID\n- `GET /api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` — Get entity display status\n\n**Key Annotations:**\n- `@RestController`\n- `@RequestMapping(\"/api/v1/entities\")`\n- `@PostMapping`, `@GetMapping`\n- `@PathVariable`, `@RequestBody`\n- `@Resource` for dependency injection\n\n**Request/Response Patterns:**\n- POST endpoints accept `@RequestBody` DTOs\n- GET endpoints accept `@PathVariable Long id`\n- All responses wrapped in `ResultDTO<T>` generic wrapper\n- Null safety: returns `ResultDTO.error()` on entity not found\n\n**Error Handling Style:**\n- Null checks with explicit error responses\n- Maps entity state to display status with switch statements\n- Simple, defensive coding (null-safe defaults)\n\n**Constraint (Important):**\n- Comment explicitly states controller must NOT import `com.fortinet.nac.ingestion.repository.*` — all data access must go through `@Service` layer\n\n---\n\n### 2. **EntityService** (Interface + Implementation)\n\n**Interface File:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityService.java`\n\n**Implementation File:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java`\n\n**Key Method Signatures:**\n```java\n// Basic CRUD\nEntity getById(Long id);\nvoid save(Entity entity);\nvoid saveBatch(Collection<Entity> entityList);\n\n// Query & State\nPagination<Entity> queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req);\nboolean isProcessingFinished(Long entityId);\nboolean updateProcessingState(Entity fresh);\n\n// Stuck entity recovery\nList<Entity> findStuckEntities(Duration staleThreshold, int maxCount);\n\n// **REPROCESS-RELATED METHODS** (Core for new endpoint)\nMarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess();  // Batch mark INIT in chunks\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, int limit);\nEntityProcessLockInfo findProcessLockInfoById(Long id);\nboolean claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id);  // Atomic INIT → RUNNING\nboolean updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state);\n```\n\n**Reprocess Semantics:**\n- **\"Policy Reprocess\"** = re-running policy enforcement on existing entities\n- **Workflow:**\n  1. Mark entities with `reprocessState = INIT` via `markAllForReprocess()`\n  2. `PolicyReprocessJob` scans for INIT entities\n  3. Atomic claim: `claimInitEntityForReprocess()` moves INIT → RUNNING (prevents race conditions)\n  4. Reset entity processing state (stage → PENDING, code → 0, result → \"{}\") \n  5. Run state machine through full policy pipeline\n  6. Update final state: SUCCESS (enforced) or FAILED based on state machine result\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- `@Transactional` with `PROPAGATION_REQUIRES_NEW` for isolation\n- Batch processing with configurable `policy.reprocess.mark-init-batch-size` (default 1000)\n- Metrics collection: `policy_reprocess_mark_init_last_failed_batches`, `policy_reprocess_mark_init_run_seconds`\n- Error resilience: batch failures don't stop processing; cursor moves forward\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Reprocess-Related Code**\n\n**Key Files Found:**\n\n1. **PolicyController:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/B/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/controller/PolicyController.java`\n   - Single endpoint: `POST /api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` (no request body)\n   - Calls `entityService.markAllForReprocess()`\n   - Publishes `PolicyReprocessRequestedEvent` for immediate async